eventDetails.eventItemValue: Remove and re-insert the connection module. Verify that the connection module is installed in interconnect bay 1 or 4. members.description: The interconnect is currently configured for dual domain but communication with its partner interconnect has failed.

eventDetails.eventItemValue: Ensure that a SAS interconnect is inserted and powered on in both bays 1 and 4.  Perform a reset (soft) of the interconnect {"name":"CZJ9260730, interconnect 4","uri":"/rest/sas-interconnects/TWT012W03L"}.  If the problem persists,  perform a reset (hard) of the same interconnect {"name":"CZJ9260730, interconnect 4","uri":"/rest/sas-interconnects/TWT012W03L"}.

User Action: If cpqSsBoxTempStatus is `degraded(3)` or `failed(4)`, shutdown the storage system as soon as possible. Ensure that the storage system environment is being cooled properly and that no components are overheated.
